    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><add>Hebrew&#47;Italian</add></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><list type="ordered">
			<head>Addressed on the outside to&#58;</head>
			<item n="1">&#40;in Hebrew&#41; To the hands of the princes&#44; the wise&#44;<lb/> the exalted&#44; etc&#44; in the holy congregation of <placeName>Phila&#45;<lb/>delphia</placeName>&#44; God bless them all together. May they live<lb/> forever and ever.</item>
			<item n="2">&#40;in Italian&#41; To the gentlemen&#44; heads of the Israe&#45;<lb/>lite nation and the Grand Rabbi in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</item>
			</list></p>
			<p></p>
			<p>&#40;Hebrew&#41;</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>The eve of Rosh Hashonah 1850&#63;</date></p>
			<p>Wise and understanding men&#44; sons of <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44;<lb/> merciful the sons of the merciful&#44; that is the gentle&#45;<lb/>men&#44; treasurers&#44; the princes of the community who<lb/> are in the congregation of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44; also the ex&#45;<lb/>alted wise men who pursue righteousness and<lb/> kindness&#44; and&#44; at their head&#44; the great and learned</p>
			<p>&#42; May God grant them everlasting life.<lb/> Peace and life to you&#44; I direct my prayer that<lb/> God may extend to you many days and years of<lb/> life&#44; wealth&#44; and the glory of children&#44; and every<lb/> thing that is good&#44; amen. A year ago I sent<lb/> you a letter and a new book&#44; and I begged of you&#44;<lb/> that the righteous ones among you send a gift</p>
			<p>&#42; The name is omitted and a space left for it. This was<lb/> evidently a circular letter but the writer did not<lb/> know the name of the rabbi of the town.</p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p>to us. Because of two great fires which<lb/> took place in our town&#44; <placeName>Ismir</placeName>&#44; we are lack&#45;<lb/>ing in everything. We have become very poor&#44;<lb/> and&#44; especially I&#44; suffered great losses. Five<lb/> big houses which were used for houses of study&#44;<lb/> all of them filled with books&#44; were all burned<lb/> down&#44; even the clothing and furniture&#44; Also the<lb/> dowry of two grown up daughters was burnt&#44;<lb/> and it is necessary to make everything all<lb/> over again. Because of all this&#44; I beg and<lb/> implore that you&#44; Children of <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; have pity<lb/> upon me&#44; and&#44; because of this&#44; you will all earn<lb/> life and children&#44; and children&#39;s children&#44;<lb/> with great wealth and honor and strength<lb/> and peace.</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Hayyim Malaggi&#44; Rabbi</persName></p>
			<p><placeName>Ismir</placeName> is somewhere near <placeName>Salonica</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
